re modems and noisy lines i used to have a lot of line noise problems with my baud modem what was sudgested to me was to put a toriod transformer on the line this is easily done by getting a large toroid core from your local electronics shop a toroid core is a ceramic metal donut and wind the telephone line in through the center of the core and out around the outside five or six times this is a easy and cheap fix that does not have the hassels of having to use sofware to fix a hardware problem talk to yah later mark mark zander sheridanc on ca
